header.gameNote: C-USA WOMEN'S CHAMPIONSHIP - QUARTERFINALS AT EL PASO TX

article.description: Courtney Taylor had 22 points and 10 rebounds and Jasmine Johnson hit several clutch free throws down the stretch to lead No. 22 Houston to a 67-64 win over UTEP in the quarterfinals of the Conference USA tournament.
article.headline: Cougars top Miners to reach C-USA semifinals
article.linkText: Taylor, Johnson lift No. 22 Houston past UTEP
article.story:
EL PASO, Texas --  Courtney Taylor had 22 points and 10 rebounds and Jasmine Johnson hit several clutch free throws down the stretch to lead No. 22 Houston to a 67-64 win over UTEP on Thursday night in the quarterfinals of the Conference USA tournament.

UTEP's Kelli Willingham tried for a desperation shot as the clock expired but came up short.

Lesslee Mason added 19 points and 14 rebounds for top-seeded Houston (26-4), which will face No. 4 seed Tulane in Friday's semifinals.

Dietra Calwell and Erika Warren each scored 18 points for the Miners (16-14).
